modules.description: Provides functions to convert integers into tagged types representing positive or greater-than-zero values, with safe and unsafe variants. Works with custom tagged types wrapped around integers. Used to enforce numeric constraints in financial calculations and input validation.

Provides functions to generate and manipulate intervals of integers, including creating ranges with start and end values, checking membership, and computing intersections. Works with tuples representing start and end points and lists of integer ranges. Used to validate input ranges in configuration parsing and to compute overlapping segments in scheduling algorithms.

Handles integer sequences defined by start and stop values, enabling efficient traversal and transformation without relying on lists. Supports splitting ranges for distributed processing and includes operations like fold, filter, and map. Incorporates safe and unsafe conversions between integers and constrained types, such as positive or non-zero values, ensuring type safety in critical applications. Examples include generating a range of positive integers, filtering even numbers, and splitting a large range for parallel computation.
